#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.63"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.63:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.63:0.2"
msgid "7. Migajālavagga "
msgstr "7. With Migajāla "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.63:0.3"
msgid "63. Paṭhamamigajālasutta "
msgstr "63. With Migajāla (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.36, sc1
msgctxt "sn35.63:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.63:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā migajālo yena bhagavā … pe … "
msgstr "Then Venerable Migajāla went up to the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn35.63:1.3"
msgid "ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā migajālo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.63:1.4"
msgid "“‘ekavihārī, ekavihārī’ti, bhante, vuccati. "
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of one who lives alone. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:1.5"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, ekavihārī hoti, kittāvatā ca pana sadutiyavihārī hotī”ti? "
msgstr "How is one who lives alone defined? And how is living with a partner defined?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.63:2.1"
msgid "“Santi kho, migajāla, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "“Migajāla, there are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:2.2"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them, "

#. VAR: nandī → nandi (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.63:2.3"
msgid "Tassa taṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato uppajjati nandī. "
msgstr "this gives rise to relishing. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:2.4"
msgid "Nandiyā sati sārāgo hoti; "
msgstr "When there’s relishing there’s lust. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:2.5"
msgid "sārāge sati saṃyogo hoti. "
msgstr "When there’s lust there is a fetter. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:2.6"
msgid "Nandisaṃyojanasaṃyutto kho, migajāla, bhikkhu sadutiyavihārīti vuccati. "
msgstr "A mendicant who is fettered by relishing is said to live with a partner. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: text entirely omits kaya and mano
msgctxt "sn35.63:2.7"
msgid "… pe … "
msgstr "There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.63:2.8"
msgid "Santi kho, migajāla, jivhāviññeyyā rasā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "There are thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:2.9"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them, "

msgctxt "sn35.63:2.10"
msgid "Tassa taṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato uppajjati nandī. "
msgstr "this gives rise to relishing. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:2.11"
msgid "Nandiyā sati sārāgo hoti; "
msgstr "When there’s relishing there’s lust. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:2.12"
msgid "sārāge sati saṃyogo hoti. "
msgstr "When there’s lust there is a fetter. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:2.13"
msgid "Nandisaṃyojanasaṃyutto kho, migajāla, bhikkhu sadutiyavihārīti vuccati. "
msgstr "A mendicant who is fettered by relishing is said to live with a partner. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: manussarāhasseyyakāni → manussarāhaseyyakāni (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.63:2.14"
msgid "Evaṃvihārī ca, migajāla, bhikkhu kiñcāpi araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevati appasaddāni appanigghosāni vijanavātāni manussarāhasseyyakāni paṭisallānasāruppāni; "
msgstr "A mendicant who lives like this is said to live with a partner, even if they frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest that are quiet and still, far from the madding crowd, remote from human settlements, and fit for retreat. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:2.15"
msgid "atha kho sadutiyavihārīti vuccati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.63:2.16"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn35.63:2.17"
msgid "Taṇhā hissa dutiyā, sāssa appahīnā. "
msgstr "For craving is their partner, and they haven’t given it up. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:2.18"
msgid "Tasmā ‘sadutiyavihārī’ti vuccati. "
msgstr "That’s why they’re said to live with a partner. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.37, sc3
msgctxt "sn35.63:3.1"
msgid "Santi ca kho, migajāla, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:3.2"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them, "

msgctxt "sn35.63:3.3"
msgid "Tassa taṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato nandī nirujjhati. "
msgstr "relishing ceases. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:3.4"
msgid "Nandiyā asati sārāgo na hoti; "
msgstr "When there’s no relishing there’s no lust. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:3.5"
msgid "sārāge asati saṃyogo na hoti. "
msgstr "When there’s no lust there’s no fetter. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:3.6"
msgid "Nandisaṃyojanavisaṃyutto kho, migajāla, bhikkhu ekavihārīti vuccati … pe … "
msgstr "A mendicant who is not fettered by relishing is said to live alone. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.63:3.7"
msgid "santi ca kho, migajāla, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe … "
msgstr "There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.63:3.8"
msgid "santi ca kho, migajāla, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "There are thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:3.9"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them, "

msgctxt "sn35.63:3.10"
msgid "Tassa taṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato nandī nirujjhati. "
msgstr "relishing ceases. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:3.11"
msgid "Nandiyā asati sārāgo na hoti; "
msgstr "When there’s no relishing there’s no lust. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:3.12"
msgid "sārāge asati saṃyogo na hoti. "
msgstr "When there’s no lust there’s no fetter. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.63:3.13"
msgid "Nandisaṃyojanavippayutto kho, migajāla, bhikkhu ekavihārīti vuccati. "
msgstr "A mendicant who is not fettered by relishing is said to live alone. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:3.14"
msgid "Evaṃvihārī ca, migajāla, bhikkhu kiñcāpi gāmante viharati ākiṇṇo bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīhi upāsakehi upāsikāhi rājūhi rājamahāmattehi titthiyehi titthiyasāvakehi. "
msgstr "A mendicant who lives like this is said to live alone, even if they live in the neighborhood of a village crowded by monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen; by rulers and their ministers, and teachers of other paths and their disciples. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:3.15"
msgid "Atha kho ekavihārīti vuccati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.63:3.16"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn35.63:3.17"
msgid "Taṇhā hissa dutiyā, sāssa pahīnā. "
msgstr "For craving is their partner, and they have given it up. "

msgctxt "sn35.63:3.18"
msgid "Tasmā ‘ekavihārī’ti vuccatī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s why they’re said to live alone.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.63:3.19"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

